@startuml
title Listening Assessment MP3 Splitting System Architecture

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Content Team" as ContentTeam

component "Admin Upload Interface\nMP3 upload and job trigger" as Upload
storage "MP3 Storage\nUploaded source audio files" as StorageInput

package "Audio Processing Service" {
  component "Audio Processing Engine\nWaveform analysis\nSilence detection\nBoundary detection" as Engine
  component "Timestamp Inference Module" as Timestamp
  component "Validation & Quality Check Layer" as Validation
  component "FFmpeg Segmentation Engine" as Segmentation
}

database "Segmented MP3 Storage" as Storage
component "Listening Assessment App\nContent delivery" as App

ContentTeam --> Upload
Upload --> StorageInput
StorageInput --> Engine
Engine --> Timestamp
Timestamp --> Validation
Validation --> Segmentation
Segmentation --> Storage
Storage --> App

note right of Engine
Design Decision:
LLM-based timestamp extraction was evaluated first,
but final split points were determined by waveform-based
signal analysis for higher precision.
end note

@enduml
